author: leosimons
msg: Make pylid support multiple include (-i) arguments, include stats for files without tests, and change how it outputs things a little.
* bin/pylid-0.3/test/test_coverage.py: unit tests for the new -i support.

* bin/pylid-0.3/pylid.py: allow multiple include paths for annotation. Make Tester import all modules on the include path if annotations are called for, so that files which lack testing are looked at as well. Make output a little less verbose, omitting details on problematic lines, and writing annotation data to files (with a new --logdir option to specify where) instead of using a pager to look through them.
